<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">Thank you! We try and take case of most of these bugs and edge cases. I think the ones that have been most useful are:<p>1. Race conditions. There are some weird conditions to handle around if a user makes it back to your app post-payment before the webhook, or if they click twice on a purchase button accidentally.<p>2. Keeping usage reset cycles in sync with billing cycles. We had a bunch of weird cases to solve in February as it&#x27;s a shorter month.<p>3. Handling annual plans that have monthly usage billing cycles. Or just handling anything to do with transitioning between annual and yearly billing.<p>Theo&#x27;s approach is awesome and a very similar architecture to what we have.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368486&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44365620%2344368486" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
